title: League Down Under Podcast
body:
Greetings friends!

My name is mooshu and I recently started a podcast about League of Legends Oceania with my friend Eddy 'Fatcat' Sellers who is currently the manager of the Chiefs. Eddy is a high ELO player and has been a part of the professional scene for a while now, so he as unique insight and has a lot of interesting thoughts to contribute. I myself am a Silver II fiend! who's a League of Legends enthusiast and is keen to support the OPL teams this season.

On the podcast we discuss: 
- The Oceanic Pro League, wrapping up the week's games and plays as well as predictions for the following week
- The Oceanic Challenger Series, 
- Patch Notes
- Player Interviews (coming soon!)
-  Anything else we find funny or interesting :D

If this sounds like something you might be interested in check us out on:
[This week's episode: "#4 League Down Under: We're Back, Baby!"](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ksTiHJrTt98&list=PL8lzPkToerc0RylBfE6YPKVRW_INK6430&index=4)

[Our Site](https://leaguedu.wordpress.com/) / [YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL8lzPkToerc0RylBfE6YPKVRW_INK6430) / [iTunes](http://apple.co/1TkimZT )

At the moment we put our episodes out weekly on Thursday night/Friday morning and will be moving towards streaming it in the near future.

If you have any feedback or would like to get in contact with Eddy or myself, post a reply or hit us up on Twitter: [Eddy](https://twitter.com/fatcatoce), [mooshu](https://twitter.com/mooshuman)

Cheers Guys!
